{{Infobox Person | name = Joseph Girzone | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = 1930 | birth_place = [[Albany, New York]] | residence = [[Altamont, Albany County, New York|Altamont, New York]] | nationality = [[United States|American]] | occupation = [[Writer]], retired [[Priesthood (Catholic Church)|Catholic priest]] | religion = [[Roman Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] }}
Father '''Joseph Girzone''' (born 1930) is an American [[writer]], and most notable as the author of the ''Joshua'' series. Girzone was born in [[Albany, New York]], to parents Peter and Margaret Girzone. He entered the [[Carmelites|Carmelite Order]] in 1948{{Fact|date=January 2008}} and was ordained as a [[Roman Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[priest]] in 1955.<ref name=girzone-site>{{cite web |url= http://www.randomhouse.com/features/girzone/author.html |title= Joseph F. Girzone: About the Author |accessdate= 2008-01-08 |year=2005 |publisher= Random House, Inc. }}</ref> After serving as pastor for various [[New York]] churches, he retired from the active priesthood in 1981<ref name=girzone-site /> for health reasons.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.wellsprings.com.sg/nzc/index.php?main_page=product_info&products_id=9221 |title= MY STRUGGLE WITH FAITH by Joseph F. Girzone |accessdate= 2008-01-08 |year= 2006 |publisher= Wellsprings Catholic Books }}</ref> Following his retirement, he embarked on a second career as a full-time writer and speaker.<ref name=girzone-site /> Joseph Girzone now lives in [[Altamont, Albany County, New York|Altamont, New York]].<ref name=girzone-site />
In 1995 he established the Joshua Foundation, "an organization dedicated to making Jesus better known throughout the world."<ref name=girzone-site />
==Writings== *''Kara : The Lonely Falcon'' (1979) *''Joshua'' (1983) *''Joshua and the Children'' (1989) *''Joshua and the Shepherd'' (1990) *''Joshua In The Holy Land'' (1993) *''Never Alone'' (1994) *''Joshua and the City'' (1995) *''What is God?'' (1996)<ref>http://www.randomhouse.com/features/girzone/bkshelf.html Retrieved: 27 Jan 2009</ref> *''Joey: An inspiring true story of faith and forgiveness'' (1997) *''A Portrait of Jesus'' (1998) *''Joshua : The Homecoming'' (1999) *''Jesus, His Life and Teachings: As Recorded by His Friends Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John'' (2000) *''The Parables of Joshua'' (2001) *''The Messenger'' (2002) *''Trinity: A New Living Spirituality'' (2002) *''Joshua in a Troubled World : A Story for Our Time'' (2005) *''My Struggle with Faith'' (2006) *''Joshua's Family'' (2007) *(Introduction by Joseph F. Girzone) ''Colors of the Spirit'' by Dorothy K. Ederer, [[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]], 1998. ISBN 978-0385-48848-8
